d packages plus `agentcube.models`\n273: \n274: ---\n275: \n276: ## Functional Testing Results\n277: \n278: ### Import Test\n279: ```python\n280: >>> from agentcube import app, __version__, PackRuntime, BuildRuntime, PublishRuntime, InvokeRuntime\n281: >>> print(__version__)\n282: '0.1.0'\n283: ```\n284: **Status: ✅ PASS**\n285: \n286: ### CLI Help Test\n287: ```\n288: $ python -m agentcube.cli.main --help\n289: Usage: python -m agentcube.cli.main [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...\n290: \n291: AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management\n292: \n293: Options:\n294:   --version            Show version and exit\n295:   --verbose  -v        Enable verbose output\n296:   --help               Show this message and exit.\n297: \n298: Commands:\n299:   pack      Pack an agent workspace for building and publishing.\n300:   build     Build an agent image from the packaged workspace.\n301:   publish   Publish an agent to the AgentCube platform or Kubernetes.\n302:   invoke    Invoke an agent with a payload.\n303:   status    Check the status of a deployed agent.\n304: ```\n305: **Status: ✅ PASS**\n306: \n307: ### Pack Command Help Test\n308: ```\n309: $ python -m agentcube.cli.main pack --help\n310: Options:\n311:   --workspace    -f      TEXT     Path to the agent workspace directory [default: .]\n312:   --agent-name           TEXT     Override the agent name\n313:   --language             TEXT     Programming language (python, java)\n314:   --entrypoint           TEXT     Override the entrypoint command\n315:   --port                 INTEGER  Port to expose in the Dockerfile\n316:   --build-mode           TEXT     Build strategy: local or cloud\n317:   --description          TEXT     Agent description\n318:   --output               TEXT     Output path for packaged workspace\n319:   --verbose                       Enable detailed logging\n320:   --help                          Show this message and exit.\n321: ```\n322: **Status: ✅ PASS**\n323: \n324: ---\n3