nting passes (`ruff`)\n305: - [ ] Documentation complete with docstrings\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Dependencies\n310: \n311: - `typer[all]>=0.9.0` — CLI framework\n312: - `pydantic>=2.0.0` — Data validation\n313: - `pyyaml>=6.0` — YAML parsing\n314: - `rich>=13.0.0` — Progress indicators and output\n315: - `packaging>=23.0` — Version handling\n316: - `semver>=3.0.0` — Semantic versioning\n317: - `pytest>=7.4.0` — Testing framework\n318: - `pytest-cov>=4.1.0` — Coverage reporting\n319: - `pytest-mock>=3.11.0` — Mocking utilities\n320: \n321: ---\n322: \n323: ## Design Notes\n324: \n325: - **Metadata precedence:** agent_metadata.yaml → agent.yaml → metadata.yaml → create new\n326: - **Language support:** Python and Java (case-insensitive)\n327: - **Build modes:** local and cloud (case-insensitive)\n328: - **Dockerfile templates:** Language-specific with best practices\n329: - **Error handling:** _handle_error() prints red message; traceback on verbose\n330: - **Progress indication:** Rich Progress spinner during pack operation\n\n(End of file - total 330 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n\n> **AR ID:** AR-020  \n> **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n> **Language:** Python  \n> **Size:** M  \n> **Stage:** ST-3 (Design) Completed → ST-4 (Implementation)\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `pack` command validates agent workspace structure, processes metadata, handles dependencies, and optionally generates Dockerfiles to prepare agents for building and publishing. This command is the entry point for the agent lifecycle management workflow.\n\n---\n\n## ST-4.1 — Project Structure & Package Setup\n\n| # | Task | Verification | Est. |\n|---|------|--------------|------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775886379623,"end":1775886379655}}}}
